		<hr size="1">I would get the cobalt gaunts over a FBSS, this is why.</P><P>Cobalt gaunts 25 AC useless right click effect</P><P>FBSS 0 AC  approx 21% haste.</P><P>The amount of AC gain from the cobalt gaunts is huge, and your probably wearing a decent belt with AC at this time.  I will guess a TBB with 8 AC and lots of strength.  So dropping this belt makes you lose more AC and strength.  (Prime Warrior Stats)</P><P>With the FBSS you would have 18 less AC or 25 actual AC. (AC mod of 1.5)  Your strength would drop 15, and your attack would drop 15.  Your strength damage bonus per hit will now be lower.  You would swing 21% faster for less damage per hit.  The FBSS will have to be replaced at some point in time, and its no longer considered a good haste item.</P><P>With the cobalt gaunts, you can stay in battle longer.  You would have a higher chance to hit because of the increased strength, and each hit would have a slightly higher damage per hit.  The cobalt gaunts will be something you will use for a good amount of time until you get Vel armor.</P><P>My opinion,</P><P>Sprite Brokenheart<BR>60th Warlord</P><P>P.S.  If you get a chance to go to Sky Plane, go!  A decent haste belt drops there off of common mobs often.  (No Drop)  Belt of Contention.  It has like 10 ac, good stats and is 21% haste also.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
