		<hr size="1">K - here's a plan.</P><P>1) Cobalt is worth a lot more than an FBSS. Don't get ripped off. <A HREF="HTTP://www.eqprices.com" TARGET="_BLANK">www.eqprices.com</A></P><P>2) Go to Icewell Keep and get a set of Royal Frosted Velium Gauntlets - AC 15, +5 STR, +25hp (NO-DROP) they should be FREE.</P><P>3) Sell the cobalt gauntlets (9100pp on eqprices) buy the FBSS (varies per server, but AT LEAST 4,000pp less).</P><P>You are trading 10 AC in the gauntlets (with a useless proc) and 8AC in the belt (if you are using TBB) for a total of 18AC and 10 STR lost. You have gained 21% haste (VERY GOOD) and 25hp (better than a stick in yer eye).</P><P>BUT - you now have 4000pp to spend upgrading other stuff. 4000pp buys some pretty impressive firepower around my parts - 2 lammys, for instance.</P><P><BR>Another possibility is silver chitin handwraps. They have higher haste than the FBSS, have 5 AC on them, and +3ish to all saves. At least 2000pp less than Cobalt Gloves also. You will lose 20AC this way, but get more haste (~30%) and still be able to wear your waist item.</P><P>Should have around 2,000pp left over also. Upgrade your earrings or something....</P><P><BR>I personally disagree with the idea that trading 10-15AC off for 21% haste is a bad thing. My gut is telling me that ending the fight quicker (if you are the only damage dealer), having a better chance of holding aggro and taking less damage due to the mob dying quicker are worth more than 10-15AC.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
