		<hr size="1">Another thing to keep in mind - is that 15 ac out of 800 (i.e. - the proverbial drop in the bucket) worth more to you than upping your damage by a whopping 21%?  (Remember, you won't be running with no gauntlets, you'll just have some that aren't as good.)</P><P>For the 60 warrior, tests have been run on level 60 warriors who fought, then got 150 points of STR buffs, and fought the same mob again.  You know how much difference that 150 points made?  About 2%.  Also, testing has shown that the strength portion of your attack rating has NO bearing on your accuracy, just on your max (and thus average) damage.</P><P>Also, keep in mind that the upgrades from the "worthless" FBSS are all very rare and very expensive, and unless you're in an uberguild, they are VERY hard to get unless you're a rogue.</P><P>--------------------<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=481" target=_blank>Hizuka</a><BR>Swifttail Disciple<BR>Initiate of the Celestial Fists<BR>Innoruuk Server<BR><BR>"I do not feel obliged to believe that the same God who has endowed us with sense, reason, and intellect has intended us to forgo their use."<BR><i>- Galileo Galilei </i><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
