		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Hizuka" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=72&FN=Warrior&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1375418&TN=Cobalt+Gaunts+or+FBSS&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1382543&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Raluvin,</P><P>Actually, I have a warrior (among LOTS of others), and I know and talk shop with many skilled warriors.  In the words of a member of my server's uberguild, "Are [you] on crack?"</P><P>[/queue music]</P><P>Please allow me to introduce my self, I'm a man of wealth, and taste.  </P><P>I've been involved in the melee discussions since they started up nearly 3 years ago, back when we were trying to figure out how combat works (Wow, damage distribution isn't linear?!?).  I read the original post about Ghetto Bashing, I remember all the charts and research figuring out damage distribution.  I was around when people were realizing that AC acutally helped far more than stats.  I also, in agonizing detail, remember reading threads on monk, ranger, warrior, and paladin forums discussing the pros and cons of trading off ac/hp/stats for haste.</P><P>[/SympathyForTheDevil]</P><P>Yes, I took most of a year off, meaning I missed the launch of Velious.  However, I still know a number of uberwarriors on my server, and talk shop with them.  The consensus of EVERY skilled melee player I've discussed this with is that haste > alles, thanks to both extra damage, and in case of warriors, extra taunt.</P><P>Since the concept of haste is obviously utterly beyond you (how in the WORLD can you say you've played 3 years and still not understand such a simple concept?), I'll lay it out for you using simple terms.</P><P>The main way rangers, rogues, and monks taunt off warriors is through outdamaging them, and in case of monks, attacking faster and more often (and rangers, snare, but that can easily be controlled).  Now if the rangers, rogues and monks get an FBSS and the warrior chooses not to, guess what?  They just upped damage by 21%, meaning they're going to draw aggro a HELL of a lot more, meaning they have to stop attacking for longer periods of time (You have to stop attacking to either evade or feign), and they have to do it longer.  Basically, they're forced to negate the advantage given them by their new sash because the WARRIOR felt taking 1 less damage per hit was worth more than the group doing damage faster.</P><P>Now if the monks, rogues, rangers, and warriors ALL get an FBSS, then the warrior's damage and aggro from attacks goes up apace with the other melee, and he thus has no more difficulty retaining aggro than he did before.  And if the warrior gets a sash, but is with melees who don't have a haste item, then it's absurdly easy to retain aggro, as a hasted warrior will generally equal or exceed the damage of an unhasted monk.  He'll be closer to unhasted rogue damage, meaning they have to evade less often, and he'll bury the unhasted ranger.</P><P>So, in summary, haste for warriors makes the entire group's life easier, as it allows the warrior to do more damage AND retain aggro that much more.</P><P>Contrast this to skipping over the FBSS in order to gain appx 15 ac, when base ac is 820.  Now we're looking at that 15 ac being 1.83% of the warrior's total AC.  That ac will typically result in 0.5% to 1.0% less damage taken over all, if that much.  In exchange, you'll do about 17% less damage than with the FBSS, and you'll have a MUCH harder time retaining aggro.</P><P>Is that truly so hard to understand?  If you don't believe me on the value of 1.83% of your armor, that's easy to test.  Figure out how much AC that is for you, and run tests with that difference.  See for yourself.</P><P>Next time you play a character to 60, I would recommend you actually learn the basicis, which is what haste is to a melee.</P><P>I have nearly 400 levels played over multiple accounts, have been in the game since 3/16/99, and generally have solid foundations on all aspects of game play, thanks to following boards dedicated to every type of class since the game came out as well as playing those classes to high level.  Yes, my monk isn't 60, mainly because I got burned out a bit, as well as the fact that my guild raids all night every night.  My last XP hunt was 3 months ago - when I turned 54.</P><P>Last I checked, this board is for discussing warriors, not for warriors only.  Take your elitist attitude and shove it.</P><P>--------------------<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=481" target=_blank>Hizuka</a><BR>Swifttail Disciple<BR>Initiate of the Celestial Fists<BR>Innoruuk Server<BR><BR>"I do not feel obliged to believe that the same God who has endowed us with sense, reason, and intellect has intended us to forgo their use."<BR><i>- Galileo Galilei </i><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
