 with a twink.  </P><P>I am not disrespecting your knowledge (or your friends knowledge) on how or why's to be a warrior.  I cannot play most classes, monk, cleric, warrior - thats me. </P><P>I am however specialised in the warrior class and most of my focus has been applied on development of me within my class.  Anyone can say that have 6 60 level characters, but can anyone say that they have truely mastered their class? </P><P>I for one, cannot...I still think there is a lot to learn about pushing the bounderies of my class and fitting in a lot better.  </P><P>The only two people that I know that have mastered their classes are Asky (60 Monk) and Banelion (60 Paladin), the rest of the people I know still need work.  This is not being derogatory, but more based on personal experience.</P><P>Once again, I apologise for any confusion and consider the matter closed.  </P><P>Raluvin Shadowsteele<BR>Level 60 Warlord <BR>Dragons of St.George<BR>Quellious  </P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
